#: ../../doc_files/content/numericalProcedures/hidden_covars.rst:2
msgid "Preventing \"hidden\" covariances"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/content/numericalProcedures/hidden_covars.rst:4
msgid ""
"For the following, it is assumed now that the arithmetic expression for "
"the output quantity :math:`y` containing several expressions, e.g., "
":math:`{\\ a}_{1},\\ a_{2},a_{3}`, each of which being functions of input"
" quantities :math:`x_{i}`. Often, the uncertainties :math:`{u(a}_{1}),\\ "
"\\ u(a_{2}),{\\ u(a}_{3})` are calculated first from which then "
":math:`u(y\\left( {\\ a}_{1},\\ a_{2},a_{3} \\right))` is derived. If, "
"however, there are some of the input quantities :math:`x_{i}`, contained "
"in more than one of the expressions :math:`{\\ a}_{1},\\ a_{2},a_{3}`, "
"then \"hidden\" or \"overlooked\" covariances exist between some of the "
":math:`{\\ a}_{1},\\ a_{2},a_{3}`, which would have to be considered "
"afterwards."
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/content/numericalProcedures/hidden_covars.rst:16
msgid ""
"This problem does not occur during the uncertainty calculations within "
"UncertRadio, because there the partial derivatives in its uncertainty "
"propagation are always build from the equation of the output quantity. It"
" is shown below, why this avoids the above problem."
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/content/numericalProcedures/hidden_covars.rst:21
msgid ""
"The ansatz for the uncertainty propagation with partial derivatives which"
" refer to the output quantity :math:`y = y({\\ a}_{1}(\\mathbf{x}),\\ "
"a_{2}(\\mathbf{x}),a_{3}(\\mathbf{x}))`, is formulated as follows with "
"the vector :math:`\\mathbf{x}` of input quantities:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/content/numericalProcedures/hidden_covars.rst:27
msgid "At first, the square within the sum is evaluated:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/content/numericalProcedures/hidden_covars.rst:29
msgid ""
"u^{2}(y) = \\sum_{i = 1}^{ni}{\\left( \\frac{\\partial y}{\\partial "
"x_{i}} \\right)^{2}u^{2}\\left( x_{i} \\right)}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/content/numericalProcedures/hidden_covars.rst:32
msgid ""
"u^{2}(y) = \\sum_{i = 1}^{ni}{\\left( \\sum_{j = 1}^{3}{\\frac{\\partial "
"y}{\\partial a_{j}}\\frac{\\partial a_{j}}{\\partial x_{i}}} "
"\\right)^{2}u^{2}\\left( x_{i} \\right)}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/content/numericalProcedures/hidden_covars.rst:35
msgid ""
"\\sum_{i = 1}^{ni}{\\left( \\frac{\\partial y}{\\partial "
"a_{1}}\\frac{\\partial a_{1}}{\\partial x_{i}} + \\frac{\\partial "
"y}{\\partial a_{2}}\\frac{\\partial a_{2}}{\\partial x_{i}} + "
"\\frac{\\partial y}{\\partial a_{3}}\\frac{\\partial a_{3}}{\\partial "
"x_{i}} \\right)^{2}u^{2}\\left( x_{i} \\right)}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/content/numericalProcedures/hidden_covars.rst:39
msgid ""
"Now, the summation over :math:`i` is performed for each of the six terms,"
" while at the same time the partial derivatives of :math:`y` by "
":math:`a_{j}` are factored out of the sums:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/content/numericalProcedures/hidden_covars.rst:43
msgid ""
"\\begin{eqnarray}\n"
"    u^{2}(y) = \\sum_{i = 1}^{n_i} & & \\left( \\frac{\\partial "
"y}{\\partial a_{1}}\\frac{\\partial a_{1}}{\\partial x_{i}} "
"\\right)^{2}u^{2}\\left( x_{i} \\right) + \\\\\n"
"    && \\left( \\frac{\\partial y}{\\partial a_{2}}\\frac{\\partial "
"a_{2}}{\\partial x_{i}} \\right)^{2}u^{2}\\left( x_{i} \\right) + \\\\\n"
"    && \\left( \\frac{\\partial y}{\\partial a_{3}}\\frac{\\partial "
"a_{3}}{\\partial x_{i}} \\right)^{2}u^{2}\\left( x_{i} \\right) + \\\\\n"
"\n"
"    && 2\\left( \\frac{\\partial y}{\\partial a_{1}}\\frac{\\partial "
"a_{1}}{\\partial x_{i}} \\right)\\left( \\frac{\\partial y}{\\partial "
"a_{2}}\\frac{\\partial a_{2}}{\\partial x_{i}} \\right)u^{2}\\left( x_{i}"
" \\right) + \\\\\n"
"    && 2\\left( \\frac{\\partial y}{\\partial a_{1}}\\frac{\\partial "
"a_{1}}{\\partial x_{i}} \\right)\\left( \\frac{\\partial y}{\\partial "
"a_{3}}\\frac{\\partial a_{3}}{\\partial x_{i}} \\right)u^{2}\\left( x_{i}"
" \\right) + \\\\\n"
"    && 2\\left( \\frac{\\partial y}{\\partial a_{2}}\\frac{\\partial "
"a_{2}}{\\partial x_{i}} \\right)\\left( \\frac{\\partial y}{\\partial "
"a_{3}}\\frac{\\partial a_{3}}{\\partial x_{i}} \\right)u^{2}\\left( x_{i}"
" \\right)\n"
"\\end{eqnarray}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/content/numericalProcedures/hidden_covars.rst:58
msgid ""
"Now, each individual sum over :math:`i` is representing a variance or a "
"covariance of the expressions :math:`{\\ a}_{1},\\ a_{2},a_{3}`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/content/numericalProcedures/hidden_covars.rst:61
msgid ""
"u^{2}(y) = &\\left( \\frac{\\partial y}{\\partial a_{1}} "
"\\right)^{2}u^{2}\\left( a_{1} \\right) +\n"
"           \\left( \\frac{\\partial y}{\\partial a_{2}} "
"\\right)^{2}u^{2}\\left( a_{2} \\right) +\n"
"           \\left( \\frac{\\partial y}{\\partial a_{3}} "
"\\right)^{2}u^{2}\\left( a_{3} \\right) + \\\\\n"
"           &2\\frac{\\partial y}{\\partial a_{1}}\\frac{\\partial "
"y}{\\partial a_{2}} cov(a_{1},a_{2}) +\n"
"            2\\frac{\\partial y}{\\partial a_{1}}\\frac{\\partial "
"y}{\\partial a_{3}}cov(a_{1},a_{3}) + \\\\\n"
"           & 2\\frac{\\partial y}{\\partial a_{2}}\\frac{\\partial "
"y}{\\partial a_{3}}cov(a_{2},a_{3})"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/content/numericalProcedures/hidden_covars.rst:70
msgid ""
"Usually, a \"hand-made\" uncertainty propagation by first applying a "
"decomposition of :math:`y` into expressions or functions :math:`a_{j}`, "
"only the first three terms in Eq. (6) are used, because covariances "
"between the :math:`a_{j}` often are not expected; this may explain the "
"term \"hidden\" covariances."
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/content/numericalProcedures/hidden_covars.rst:76
msgid ""
"The result of Eq. (6) is just the one which has to be expected when "
"\"hidden\" covariances between the :math:`a_{j}` are explicitly taken "
"into account. This demonstrates that these covariances are considered by "
"UncertRadio, automatically, only because it uses within its uncertainty "
"evaluation according to Eq. (1), partial derivatives directly of the "
"output quantity."
msgstr ""

